Key Match Events: David Warner top-scored with 39 from 16 balls
Adam Zampa accounted for both of England's openers - Jos Buttler and Phil Salt
Post-Match Reflections: Australia outplayed England in Barbados to leave the defending champions sweating on their qualification for the Super 8s
Miscellaneous Highlights: The dimensions played a major role at Kensington Oval: one square boundary was nine metres shorter than the other, measured at just 58m
Others: England will almost certainly need to beat both Oman (on Thursday) and Namibia (on Saturday), but even then would likely have to rely on net run rate to qualify for the second round ahead of Scotland
